   103	
   104	**Notification is per-write, in the writer's stack, value-blind (D5/D10/
   105	D13)**, over K0∪K1 with a per-walk visited generation (unions of per-world
   106	acyclic graphs can cycle, I32). Walks dispatch no user code — that is a
   107	proved property, so walks cannot nest. Per-(watcher, slot) dedup re-arms at
   108	render (I5/C4). New edges propagate touched bits through existing out-edges
   109	and retroactively deliver still-live slots through the new path (I23).
   110	Mount fixup schedules value-blind into every live non-included touched
   111	token (I13), then compares the mount's rendered value against **its own
   112	world fast-forwarded** (`w_fx`: retired-and-locked visibility at now, the
   113	pass's mask at its pin) — inequality is by construction attributable to
   114	committed-side changes the render missed, so firing is always right and
   115	C9 mounts never double-render (I43).
   116	
   117	**Suspense** keys thenables by fork lineage (D11) and validates by content:
   118	the flattened prefix of (atom fp + reducer effStamp + value) and (computed,
   119	effStamp) positions; on a stamp move it re-folds and compares *value*
   120	before refetching (I35) — content-neutral flips keep the settled resource.
   121	
   122	**Async actions**: parking (retirement waits for the returned thenable) +
   123	continuation identity (the measured twin-build carrier, I30; AsyncContext
   124	when the host ships it; armed registration-time shims on enumerated
   125	schedulers, I36). A carrier token consulted after retirement degrades to
   126	ambient + dev warn (I37). Uncompiled vendor code writing post-await
   127	misattributes to its ambient batch — sound, bounded, dev-warned,
   128	boot-tested, support-matrixed (D17); ActionScope is the precise escape.
   129	
   130	**Lifecycle.** Retirement folds only the prefix every live pin sees;
   131	touched slots are retained until swept (I10/I39); saturation force-clears
   132	the oldest fully-retired slot and flips excluded pinned passes to
   133	world-path-only. Quiescence refreshes K1-touched committed-observed nodes
   134	into K0 before K1 resets; twice-writing targets are exempted with their
   135	full reverse-reachable cone carried (I42). Every counter reset pairs with
   136	an epoch/generation guard (I8/I19/C13).
   137	
   138	**Numbers.** DIRECT = donor ([ARENA]: deep 0.90×, broad 0.84–0.88×,
   139	diamond 0.89×). LOGGED-quiet floor 2.4–3.8% [SPKHQ→O19] vs the ≤2% gate —
   140	pre-registered renegotiation. Carrier ≈0% unarmed, +12 ns/await armed
   141	(I30). Host-protocol boundary free, storage move 5–12% (I11) — values stay
   142	in-plane. Everything else unmeasured is a named spike (§16).
   143	
   144	## 2. Concepts (plain English, defined before use)
   145	
   146	- **K0** — the canonical kernel: the donor arena (one Int32Array plane,
   147	  interleaved node+link records, iterative walks). Holds every node's
   148	  *newest-applied* value and the newest-basis dependency edges. Closed and
   149	  monomorphic (D4); identical bytes in DIRECT and LOGGED builds except the
   150	  swapped op table.
   151	- **DIRECT / LOGGED** — the two op tables. DIRECT: donor behavior, zero
   152	  concurrency instructions. LOGGED: writes leave receipts, reads consult
   153	  routing. Swap happens once, at `registerReactBridge()` (monotonic, D1).
   154	- **receipt / tape** — {op, slot, seq} appended per LOGGED write to the
   155	  written atom's per-atom log. `op` is the set value or updater/action.
   156	- **base / baseSeq** — the folded floor of a tape: retired receipts that
   157	  every live pin sees get compacted into base.
   158	- **seq / globalSeq** — one process-wide monotone counter; write seqs,
   159	  pins, stamps, and epochs are all minted from it (I15).
   160	- **batch / token / slot** — a batch is React's unit of work (one event or
   161	  transition); the fork mints an integer token per batch (never reused
   162	  live); ≤31 live tokens (I10) intern into 5-bit **slots**; a pass's
   163	  include-set is a 32-bit **mask** of slots.
   164	- **pin** — the globalSeq value frozen at pass start; the pass observes
   165	  mask-writes only up to its pin.
   166	- **world / worldKey** — one consistent assignment of values: NEWEST (K0),
   167	  a pass world (mask, pin, lock view, epoch), or committed-for-root(r)
   168	  (retired ∪ locked-into-r). The tuple is the memo key.
   169	- **lock view** — immutable pooled record per root: `{slot, slotGen,
   170	  watermark, lockStamp}[≤31]` plus `lockViewId`; re-minted at every
   171	  lock-in and watermark advance (I34). A pass captures its root's view at
   172	  start and keeps it.
   173	- **watermark** — per (root, slot): the highest seq of that slot's writes
   174	  committed into that root (I25 — lock-in is a write-prefix, not token
   175	  membership).
   176	- **wc[s] (slot write clock)** — bumped on every write in slot s (D9).
   177	- **touched(n)** — one int32 per node: bits 0–30 = "slot s's cone reached
   178	  n through a recorded edge"; **bit 31 = TAINT** = "n's K0 cache may embed
   179	  pending state acquired through an untracked read" (§6.2). The fast path
   180	  is exactly `touched(n) == 0 ∧ …`.
   181	- **touchedList[s]** — per-slot list of nodes/effects whose touched word
   182	  gained bit s; the durable enumeration for retirement/lock flushes (I34).
   183	- **CT(n)** — "clean, no recompute needed": donor K0 status says the cache
   184	  is current on the newest basis.
   185	- **taint (bit 31)** — see touched; full rules §6.2.
   186	- **K1** — the world-edge plane: real dependency edges recorded by world
   187	  evaluations (and E-PRESERVE mirrors), add-only to quiescence.
   188	- **E-PRESERVE** — strong reading (champion R10): every edge a K0 re-track
   189	  removes while any live receipt exists anywhere is mirrored into K1.
   190	- **world memo M(n, worldKey)** — cached world evaluation with its
   191	  recorded deps, seq, fingerprints, and evaluator vector.
   192	- **fp(a, w)** — per-atom fingerprint: `max(newest w-visible entry seq,
   193	  baseSeq, retireVisStamp(a), lockTerm(a, w))`. (Reducer identity moved to
   194	  the evaluator vector — L3.)
   195	- **retireVisStamp(a)** — stamp minted at every retirement fold touching a
   196	  (I21).
   197	- **lockStamp / lockTerm** — lockStamp(root, slot) minted at first lock-in
   198	  and every advance; lockTerm(a, w) = max lockStamp over w's lock-view
   199	  slots holding a w-visible entry of a (computed during the fold).
   200	- **evaluator / effStamp / evaluator vector** — an evaluator is a computed
   201	  fn or a reducer. effStamp(e, pass) = the stamp staged in this pass for e,
   202	  else the committed stamp. The vector is the flattened
   203	  [(evaluatorId, effStamp)] traversed by an evaluation (memos and suspense
   204	  prefixes record it; §8.2).
   205	- **staging / lineage stage cache / F9 / promotion** — §11.1. A **lineage**
   206	  is the fork-minted render-lineage identity (per root × batch-set, stable
   207	  across restarts/replays — D11, fork F5).
   208	- **committedAdvanceSeq** — L6: one counter bumped at retirement folds,
   209	  lock view re-mints, and promotions; fast-outs only, never validity.
   210	- **walkGen / lastWalk** — per-walk visited generation and its per-record
   211	  column (I32).
   212	- **fastPathDisabled(pass)** — saturation spillover flag (I39): the pass
   213	  routes every read through the world path.
   214	- **watcher** — a mounted component's subscription record: node, setState,
   215	  lastRendered value, rendered-world snapshot (mask, pin, lockViewId),
   216	  per-slot dedup bits.
   217	- **RENDER_NEWEST** — a pass classification: no live divergence can reach
   218	  this pass (its world ≡ NEWEST), so reads serve K0 directly; revoked
   219	  (demoted to real mask/pin) by the first receipt-creating write or the
   220	  first staged evaluator (S23).
   221	- **carrier / parking / ActionScope** — async-action identity and lifetime
   222	  (§12); rungs: AsyncContext (1) / twin-build transform + shims (2) /
   223	  explicit AsyncLocalStorage opt-in (2b).
   224	- **episode / epoch** — quiescence-to-quiescence span; epochs guard every
   225	  counter reset (I8, C13).
   226	- **core effect / useSignalEffect** — core `effect()` observes NEWEST
   227	  (documented); `useSignalEffect` observes committed-for-root only (C16).
   228	
