   275	## 4. Modes and activation
   276	
   277	DIRECT: donor op table; no tapes, no touched column maintenance, no
   278	routing, no shims — zero concurrency instructions (P3), proven by CI
   279	symbol diff of the DIRECT bundle. LOGGED: activated exactly once by
   280	`registerReactBridge()` (monotonic — never keyed to watcher count, S6).
   281	Activation swaps the op-table binding at operation boundaries (closure
   282	rebuild, the measured-safe pattern [GUIDE]).
   283	
   284	Two activation rules (both restrictions are detectable at the throw site):
   285	
   286	- `registerReactBridge()` **throws if called while any evaluation, fold,
   287	  or walk frame is open** (the frame already exists for cycle detection
   288	  and I28 guards). Legal composition: register during app setup. This
   289	  closes the mid-evaluation op-table swap hole (docket: DIRECT→LOGGED
   290	  transition caches) without a transition protocol.
   291	- Caches created in DIRECT are legal LOGGED state: no receipts existed, so
   292	  every pre-swap cache embeds committed-only values; touched columns are
   293	  zero-initialized. This is the base case of TAINT-COMPLETE (§6.3) and of
   294	  invariant R (§6.4).
   295	
   296	SSR/hydration (R10): hydrate atom state by plain construction/set before
   297	`registerReactBridge()` — DIRECT-mode writes, no receipts; then register.
   298	RSC/Flight out of scope v1.
   299	
   300	## 5. Value model
   301	
   302	### 5.1 Write path (LOGGED)
   303	
   304	A write to atom `a` in ambient batch context b (fork F1; carrier-consulted
   305	per §12, liveness-checked per I37):
   306	
   307	1. Classify: token = F1's answer (or the carrier's live token); intern slot
   308	   s (minting/force-clearing per §5.4 if needed).
   309	2. **Drop check (I7/I38a)**: if `tape(a)` is empty AND base has no pending
   310	   history AND the op has world-invariant meaning (plain `set` always;
   311	   updater/reducer only when the atom's evaluator is immutable — plain
   312	   atoms, constructor reducers) AND the op evaluated against base is equal
   313	   → drop (no receipt, no walk). Stageable ReducerAtoms always append.
   314	3. Append receipt {op, s, seq=++globalSeq}; bump wc[s]; apply to K0 with
   315	   the atom's stepwise equality (keep the old reference on equal — I29).
   316	4. Add s to touched(a); **write walk**: propagate bit s from a through
   317	   K0∪K1 out-edges (monotone frontier `newBits & ~touched(n)`), appending
   318	   newly-bitted nodes/effects to touchedList[s].
   319	5. **Delivery** (D5/D10/D13): per-write, synchronous, value-blind: for
   320	   every watcher record reached by the walk whose (watcher, s) dedup bit is

