   662	## 10. Notification and delivery
   663	
   664	### 10.1 Delivery rules (settled: D5/D10/D13, I5, I23)
   665	
   666	Per-write, synchronous, in the writer's stack, value-blind. Per-(watcher,
   667	slot) dedup bits re-arm at the watcher's render. Edge-add retroactive
   668	delivery: when a new edge x→n is recorded while slots are live on x,
   669	replay each still-live slot's delivery through the new path (runInBatch
   670	per slot — I23), immediately in every non-render context, queued to the
   671	pass's yield/end edge when discovered inside a render slice. Retirement
   672	and lock-advance triggers enumerate durably via touchedList (I34); the
   673	write-time effect queue is an optimization whose consumption never removes
   674	an effect from later enumerations.
   675	
   676	### 10.2 Walk termination and atomicity (I32 + L7)
   677	
   678	Value-blind full walks (write notification; retirement notification;
   679	promotion notification) carry walkGen: bump one global counter per walk;
   680	lastWalk(record) == walkGen ⇒ skip. One int load+compare+store per visited
   681	record per walk (G-N/G-W ledger). Mark/edge-add/taint propagations need no
   682	walkGen: their `newBits & ~touched` frontier is monotone and
   683	self-terminating.
   684	
   685	**Walk atomicity (the reentrancy answer — proof, not machinery).** Claim:
   686	no walk can begin while a walk frame is open, so one global walkGen is
   687	sound. Construction — enumerate every instruction class a walk executes:
   688	record loads/stores and bit ops (no dispatch); watcher setState (React
   689	enqueues; our fork's scheduler never renders synchronously inside a
   690	setState call — flushSync inside a walk would require user code, and none
   691	runs); core-effect *enqueue* (no run — flushes drain after the write's
   692	walk returns; a flushed effect that writes starts its walk after the
   693	previous walk returned, sequentially). The only user-adjacent code near a
   694	walk is fold-frame callbacks (reducers, equality) — and fold frames are
   695	never open inside walks (folds happen at reads/retirement processing, and
   696	retirement's fold step completes before its notification step begins);
   697	inside fold frames, signal reads/writes throw (I28). Therefore no write,
   698	no evaluation, and no walk can be initiated from within a walk. ∎
   699	Dev assert: entering a walk with `walkActive` set crashes loudly (turns
   700	any future violation of this construction into a dev error, not a silent
   701	gen collision). walkGen wrap: renumber sweep row (§15).
   702	
   703	This same atomicity answers the docket's saturation attack: force-clear
   704	runs only inside `internSlot`, which runs only inside the write path,
   705	which cannot be inside a walk — so no walk can observe a half-swept
   706	touchedList (C1-X5 row 5).
   707	
   708	## 11. React bindings
   709	
   710	### 11.1 Evaluator staging, F9, promotion (I22/I31/I38/I40/I41; L4/L8)
   711	
   712	**Staging (per hook invocation with incoming (fn, deps)):**
   713	
   714	```
   715	1. deps pairwise-equal (Object.is) to the COMMITTED evaluator's deps
   716	     → use committed {fn, stamp}; no stage, no mint, no demotion.   // L4
   717	2. else deps equal to this pass frame's staged entry → reuse it.
   718	3. else deps equal to the lineage stage cache entry → reuse its
   719	     {fn, stamp}; stage it into this pass's frame.
   720	4. else mint {fn, deps, stamp: ++globalSeq}; stage into the pass frame;
   721	     update the lineage stage cache.
   722	Staging (cases 2–4) additionally: demotes a RENDER_NEWEST pass to its
   723	real (mask, pin); registers the F9 publication id on the WIP hook.
   724	```
   725	
   726	Properties: a stage exists iff deps ≠ committed's (L4) — so deps
   727	oscillation A→B→A lands back on the committed evaluator with zero mints;
   728	suspense retries and StrictMode replays hit case 1 or 3 and reuse stamps
   729	(lineage-stable, I40); the lineage stage cache is per-(lineage ×
   730	hookNode), dies at lineage death, stamps renumber per §15.
   731	
   732	**Promotion = F9 emission** (the hook *becomes current*: hidden Offscreen
   733	included, error-abandoned subtrees excluded, stale alternates rejected by
   734	generation CAS — I41), ordered before the same commit's retirement folds
   735	and layout effects (I38c). Steps:
   736	
   737	- P1: install the staged {fn, deps, stamp} as the committed evaluator —
   738	  **the stamp is installed unchanged, never re-minted** (so recorded
   739	  vectors/prefixes that saw the staged stamp still compare equal — §9.2).
   740	- P2: dirty the K0 node (commit-phase, render-pure) so the next NEWEST
   741	  read re-evaluates under the promoted closure (S23's backstop half); bump
   742	  committedAdvanceSeq.
   743	- P3 (ReducerAtom with pending receipts): re-fold K0 NEWEST under the new
   744	  committed reducer — the **ordinary** fold path with stepwise equality;
   745	  if the value moved, the **ordinary** notification walk + reconcile
   746	  checks + effect flush run in the committing context (L8; delivery lane
   747	  = the committing context's, per D5). Dev-warn retained (perf note);
   748	  differential battery keeps its swap-with-pending rows.
   749	- P4: `publicationsComplete(passId)` reclaims unpublished stages; discard
   750	  and lineage death reclaim without promotion.
   751	
   752	`useSignalEffect` fn/deps changes take **no F9 path** (D18): React's own
   753	deps contract re-fires the effect at its commit, which re-reads,
   754	re-tracks, and re-subscribes (walk C16-D).
   755	
   756	### 11.2 Mount/subscribe fixup (L2 — judge blocker 2 repaired)
   757	
   758	Runs in the mounting component's layout effect, after subscription.
   759	`w_r` = the watcher's rendered-world snapshot (mask, pin, lockViewId,
   760	captured lock view); `v_r` = its lastRendered value.
   761	
   762	```
   763	r = touched(n)
   764	if r == 0 ∧ CT(n): return                    // committed-only content (§6.3); nothing to do
   765	for each LIVE written token t with slot s = slot(t) ∈ (r & SLOTS):
   766	  if s ∈ w_r.mask ∪ w_r.lockView ∧ wc[s] ≤ w_r.pin: continue   // fully included (I43): skip
   767	  fork.runInBatch(t, setStateW)              // value-blind entanglement (I13 — never skipped by value)
   768	if committedAdvanceSeq ≤ w_r.pin ∧ root.lockViewId == w_r.lockViewId:
   769	  return                                     // fast-out: nothing committed-side moved (L6)
   770	v_fx = evaluate(n, w_fx)                     // the rendered world, fast-forwarded (below)
   771	if !isEqual(v_fx, v_r): setStateW()          // urgent pre-paint correction (C10's mandated fallback)
   772	```
   773	
   774	**w_fx (one world, no suppression predicate).** Visibility:
   775	
   776	```
   777	visible(e, w_fx) =  (e.retiredSeq ≠ ∅)                                  // committed truth at NOW
   778	                 ∨ (e.slot ∈ w_r.mask ∧ e.seq ≤ w_r.pin)               // the render's own inclusions, at its pin
   779	                 ∨ (e.slot ∈ LV_now ∧ e.seq ≤ LV_now[e.slot].watermark) // root's CURRENT lock view
   780	```
   781	
   782	Evaluators: committed (post-F9-of-this-commit, so a stage published by
   783	the mounting pass itself compares as what it rendered with — F9 precedes
   784	layout, I41). All comparisons stay on the one globalSeq line (I15's
   785	letter: two thresholds, one number line).
   786	
   787	**Why this is the I43 reconciliation (construction).** v_fx − v_r can
   788	differ only through visibility w_fx has and w_r lacked — and w_fx differs
   789	from w_r *only* on the committed side: retirements that landed after the
   790	pin (retired clause at NOW), lock-ins/advances after capture (current
   791	view), promotions (committed evaluators). Divergence from **live included
   792	tokens is folded IN, not compared against** (mask clause kept at the
   793	rendered pin), so a C9 mount inside a batch's own pass sees v_fx = v_r by
   794	purity and never double-renders; post-pin writes by live tokens are
   795	excluded from w_fx exactly because the per-token loop already scheduled
   796	their entanglement (firing urgently for them would tear the pending
   797	batch). Divergence from live non-included tokens is invisible to both
   798	sides (not retired, not in mask, not locked). So: fire ⟺ the render
   799	missed committed-side truth ⟺ exactly the retire-race/advance/promotion
   800	window I18 mandates a durable fallback for. The retired clause needs no
   801	token enumeration — retiredSeq is on the entries — so a token that
   802	retired and swept in the window is still seen (I18). S10/I13 are
   803	respected: value equality never *suppresses* a live-token corrective (the
   804	loop is value-blind and runs first); the value compare only gates the
   805	urgent committed-side correction, where equality means "no correction
   806	exists to make" — and it compares the one *joint* fast-forwarded world,
   807	so S10's per-token-projection subset trap cannot arise. ∎
   808	
   809	Cost: G-F. R-clean mounts (touched == 0 ∧ CT): zero work. Fixups: ≤
   810	|touched ∩ live non-included| runInBatch calls + (only when
   811	committedAdvanceSeq/lockViewId moved) one world evaluation.
   812	
   813	### 11.3 Watcher lifecycle
   814	
   815	Subscribe at layout (before fixup); unsubscribe at cleanup with
   816	microtask-debounced observed-count effects (R1 flap-proofing; C14
   817	double-mount nets to one). lastRendered updates at every committed render
   818	of the watcher; dedup bits re-arm at render (C4). The reconcile-at-fold
   819	backstop (§5.3 step 4) compares against lastRendered — committed-truth
   820	value compare, legal (I35 delivery/validity distinction).
   821	
   822	### 11.4 Effects
   823	
   824	`useSignalEffect` evaluates in committed-for-root(r) (world path; worldKey
   825	carries lockViewId). Flush triggers, all durable (I14/I34): root commits
   826	including every per-root lock-in/watermark advance (enumerate
   827	touchedList[advanced slot]); retirements (touchedList[slot]); settlement
   828	re-checks. Snapshot fingerprints include lockTerm, so an advance moves
   829	them; committedAdvanceSeq is an optional pre-filter (unmoved ⇒ skip the fp
   830	scan — never the reverse, S20). Core `effect()` observes NEWEST
   831	(documented contract, walked in C16).
   832	
   833	### 11.5 Hooks surface (R4)
   834	
   835	`useSignal`/`useAtom`/`useReducerAtom`/`useComputed(fn, deps)` — reads
   836	route per §6; `useComputed` staging per §11.1. Provider-free: the bridge
   837	is module-level (one fork handshake); roots register at first mount
   838	(per-root lock views live in the root registry — O7). `useSignalEffect`
   839	per §11.4. Render-phase writes throw (C14; the world-eval and render
   840	frames are distinct — yield-gap handlers are not "in render", I6).
