   842	## 12. Async actions (C12 family; D15/D17, I26/I30/I36/I37)
   843	
   844	### 12.1 Carrier rungs and scheduler shims (L5 re-scope)
   845	
   846	- **Rung 1 — AsyncContext** (feature-detected): native carrier; no build
   847	  requirement.
   848	- **Rung 2 — twin-build transform** (I30, measured: ≈0% unarmed,
   849	  +12 ns/await armed): each async fn compiles to native body +
   850	  token-carrying generator driver behind a one-null-check dispatch.
   851	  **Armed registration-time shims** (I36) on: `setTimeout`, `setInterval`,
   852	  `queueMicrotask`, `requestAnimationFrame`, `requestIdleCallback` — at
   853	  *registration*, if currentToken ≠ null, the callback is bracketed
   854	  (push(token)/finally-restore at invocation, liveness-checked per §12.2).
   855	  Unarmed or token-null registrations are never wrapped.
   856	  **MessagePort/postMessage is not shimmed** (L5): port handlers register
   857	  at boot with token null, so the champion's own registration rule already
   858	  never wrapped them — the send-time flow is a *different* semantics that
   859	  AsyncContext's event model (registration-snapshot) also does not carry.
   860	  The class is documented boundary, dev-warned, rung-uniform; ActionScope
   861	  is the precise escape. Not an S22 repeat: the transform still carries
   862	  every await; shims cover explicit host registration only.
   863	- **Rung 2b — Node AsyncLocalStorage, explicit opt-in** (server; +38%
   864	  promise-machinery cost noted, never auto-selected).
   865	
   866	**Carrier induction.** Base: the token is ambient during the action's
   867	synchronous prefix. Step: (i) every resumption of a compiled async fn
   868	passes through its driver's push/restore; (ii) every compiled async fn
   869	invoked while the token is ambient instantiates its generator under it;
   870	(iii) every callback registered through a shimmed scheduler while the
   871	token is ambient is bracketed at invocation. Residual (documented, D17):
   872	unshimmed registrars; uncompiled async functions' internal awaits. ∎
   873	
   874	### 12.2 Retired-token fallback (I37)
   875	
   876	Every carrier consult checks liveness: a token that is not live-parked
   877	(retired/settled) is treated as null — ambient classification — with a dev
   878	warning ("action continuation outlived its action"). Uniform across rungs.
   879	Parking stays keyed to the returned thenable (React parity: a late
   880	un-awaited child's update lands in its own batch). Liveness races are
   881	closed by stack-atomicity: the consult and the receipt append are one
   882	synchronous extent; retirement is also synchronous code, so no interleave
   883	exists mid-extent; each *continuation* re-enters through its own consult.
   884	
   885	### 12.3 ActionScope and realm affinity
   886	
   887	`startSignalTransition(fn(scope))`: `scope.set(atom, v)` /
   888	`scope.dispatch(ra, action)` supply the captured token explicitly
   889	(generation- and liveness-checked); `scope.runSync(fn)` enters the carrier
   890	for the synchronous extent; calls after settlement throw ("ActionScope
   891	closed"). Realm affinity: atoms, tokens, roots, scopes carry an
   892	owner-realm nonce; foreign tokens throw at runInBatch; Atom/ActionScope
   893	are not structured-cloneable (detectable restriction; ordinary worker
   894	promises unaffected).
   895	
   896	### 12.4 Boot self-test and support matrix
   897	
   898	`registerReactBridge()` arms LOGGED synchronously; the transform probe
   899	verdict lands one microtask later and throws async-loud on failure
   900	(support-matrix message); the probe covers a shimmed-scheduler round trip,
   901	per bundle pipeline. Support matrix:
