I have four concrete attack surfaces so far: abandoned fresh-node allocation, cross-root evaluator publication during an open pass, late-join fixup against a partial lock watermark, and dependency discovery after a source batch has already retired. I’m now checking each against the design’s exact lifecycle and notification clauses, and scanning every “impossible/by construction” claim before ranking them.
